## Conclusion

The biggest lesson was that alternative data is NOT always alpha-additive. No dataset is inherently useful to a non-specific trading strategy.

I started by trying to build a broad HRRR/ASOS-driven model for temperature tails. After correcting the pipeline, that broad model was less powerful than expected.
But the research process uncovered a more specific market anomaly: a subset of Kalshi temperature longshot NO contracts that showed persistent historical profitability.

The private conclusion is more comprehensive and specific. That is what I will continue tracking live.
